net.proteusframework.internet.support.xml

Class LinkHelperTagListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.core.xml.TagListener<TagListenerConfiguration>
      • net.proteusframework.internet.support.xml.LinkHelperTagListener

  • public class LinkHelperTagListener
extends TagListener<TagListenerConfiguration>
    TagListener implementation for processing cms links into external ones with optional modification of the externalized URIs.
    Example: 
     
 new LinkHelperTagListener(autowiredLinkHelper, mySite)
    .withQuerySupplier(() -> {
        final Principal p = getPrincipal(emailRecipient);
        final Map<String, String> props = new HashMap<>();
        if(p != null)
        {
            final TokenCredentials token = _appUtil.getTokenForPrincipal(p, "plan9");
            props.put(PrincipalDAO.AUTH_TOKEN_NAME, token.getToken());
        }
        return props;
    })
    .withLinkConverter((link) -> {
        try
        {
            return _notificationService.createShortenedURL(link.getURIAsString());
        }
        catch(IOException e)
        {
            _logger.error("Unable to shorted URL.", e);
        }
        return link.getURIAsString();
    });
    Author:
    Alan Holt (aholt@venturetech.net)
